Let \emph{T} denote a linear transformation of
\textbf{R}\textsuperscript{2} such that

\begin{align*}
T(b_1) = \left[ \begin{array}{c} 1 \\ 1 \end{array}\right] \quad T(b_2) = \left[ \begin{array}{c} 1 \\ 2 \end{array}\right]
\end{align*}

Find \emph{T}(\emph{b}\textsubscript{3}) and give the matrix of \emph{T}
